menu "WellD Sensor"

    config WELLD_SENSOR_ADC_CHANNEL
        int "ADC1 channel for 4-20 mA sensor"
        default 0
        range 0 6

    config WELLD_SENSOR_SHUNT_MILLIOHMS
        int "Shunt resistor value (milliohms)"
        default 100000
        range 1000 155000
        help
            Value in milliohms. 100000 = 100 Ω → 4 mA gives 0.40 V, 20 mA gives 2.00 V.
            Upper bound is 155 Ω (155000 mΩ): at 20 mA full scale that produces 3.1 V,
            the top of the ADC linear range. Higher values exceed the ESP32-C6 ADC
            absolute-maximum input of 3.6 V and will damage the GPIO pin.

    config WELLD_SENSOR_MAX_DEPTH_CM
        int "Maximum well depth (centimeters)"
        default 600
        help
            Depth at 20 mA (full-scale output of the transducer). 600 = 6 m.

    config WELLD_SENSOR_OFFSET_CM
        int "Water level offset (centimeters, signed)"
        default 0
        range -600 600
        help
            Added to the computed level after scaling. Use a negative value
            when the transducer sits below the true zero reference point
            (e.g. -50 if it hangs 50 cm below the water outlet pipe).
            Can be overridden at runtime via NVS key "welld/offset_cm".
            Both this default and any runtime value written to NVS key
            'welld/offset_cm' are clamped to the range -600 to +600 cm at
            runtime.

    config WELLD_BATT_REPORT_ENABLED
        bool "Report battery voltage over Zigbee (EP2)"
        default y
        help
            Registers Zigbee endpoint 2 (Analog Input, battery volts) and
            reports the battery voltage to the coordinator on every wakeup.
            The battery is always measured internally via the ADS1115 AIN2
            gated resistor divider for the low-battery guard, regardless of
            this option — disabling it only removes the Zigbee endpoint.

    config WELLD_BATT_DIVIDER_RATIO
        int "Battery divider ratio * 100 (e.g. 200 = 2:1 divider)"
        default 200
        range 100 1000
        help
            PCB R7/R8 = 100 kΩ / 100 kΩ divider = ratio 200 (1S board, 2026-07-19);
            VBAT range 3.0–4.2 V. Reported voltage = ADC voltage * ratio / 100.
            The AIN2 read uses the ADS1115 ±4.096 V PGA, so the 2.1 V divider
            maximum at full charge fits with margin (±2.048 V would clip).
            Used for the ADS1115 AIN2 battery divider read (the only battery
            measurement path on this hardware).

    config WELLD_BATT_FULL_MV
        int "Battery full voltage (mV)"
        default 4200
        range 3000 12000
        help
            Voltage read at 100 % state of charge. 4200 = 1S2P 18650 (4.2 V).
            Used by the Z2M converter to compute the battery percentage.
            (The low-battery send/NVS-skip guard uses WELLD_BATT_EMPTY_MV,
            not this option.)

    config WELLD_BATT_EMPTY_MV
        int "Battery empty voltage (mV)"
        default 3000
        range 2000 10000
        help
            Voltage read at 0 % state of charge. 3000 = 1S2P 18650 (3.0 V —
            also the ESP32-C6 minimum supply through the HT7333 LDO passthrough).
            When battery voltage (from ADC divider) drops at or below this
            threshold, the device skips the Zigbee send and all NVS writes and
            sleeps for the maximum interval to conserve charge.

    config WELLD_DS18B20_GPIO
        int "GPIO number for DS18B20 data line"
        default 7
        range 0 21
        help
            GPIO connected to the DS18B20 data pin via a 4.7 kΩ pull-up to 3.3 V.
            External power mode is required: connect DS18B20 VCC to 3.3 V and GND
            to GND. Parasite-power mode (VCC pin tied to GND) is not supported —
            the RMT one-wire driver does not drive a strong pull-up during
            conversion, so a parasite-powered sensor will stall and return an
            out-of-range reading that is silently discarded every wakeup.

    config WELLD_I2C_SDA_GPIO
        int "I2C SDA GPIO (ADS1115)"
        range 0 21
        default 10
        help
            GPIO number for the I2C SDA line. Used by ADS1115 (16-bit ADC,
            0x48). MAX17048 removed in an earlier hardware redesign.

    config WELLD_I2C_SCL_GPIO
        int "I2C SCL GPIO (ADS1115)"
        range 0 21
        default 11
        help
            GPIO number for the I2C SCL line.

    config WELLD_VLOOP_GPIO
        int "VLOOP 12 V boost enable GPIO (MT3608B EN)"
        range 0 21
        default 5
        help
            Drive HIGH before any 4-20 mA transducer read; hold HIGH for
            at least 10 ms to guarantee the 12 V rail is stable — the boost
            output caps (C20/C22) charge through the Q3 load-disconnect
            P-FET, so the rail settles slower than the bare MT3608B
            soft-start (< 5 ms typical). Drive LOW immediately after.
            Max ON time 100 ms per wake cycle.

    config WELLD_BATT_DIV_EN_GPIO
        int "Battery divider enable GPIO (Q2 gate)"
        range 0 21
        default 15
        help
            Drives Q2 gate (AO3400A). HIGH enables the R7/R8 resistor divider
            (100 kΩ / 100 kΩ on the 1S board) connected to ADS1115 AIN2 via
            the Q5 high-side P-FET. Drive HIGH for 1 ms
            before reading; LOW after to prevent quiescent divider drain.

    config WELLD_ADS1115_DRDY_GPIO
        int "ADS1115 ALERT/DRDY GPIO"
        range 0 21
        default 12
        help
            GPIO connected to the ADS1115 ALERT/DRDY open-drain output. The
            sensor component configures the ADS1115 in conversion-ready mode
            (Lo_thresh = 0x8000, Hi_thresh = 0x7FFF per datasheet) so the pin
            pulses LOW when each single-shot conversion completes. The GPIO is
            configured as input with the ESP32-C6 internal pull-up enabled
            (ADS1115 ALERT/DRDY is open-drain). A falling-edge ISR releases a
            binary semaphore so the sensor task can block instead of polling.
            Timeout fallback of 10 ms protects against a missing edge.

    config WELLD_SOLAR_DETECT_GPIO
        int "Solar charging detect GPIO (/CHRG, active-low)"
        range 0 21
        default 6
        help
            Input. Active-low: LOW means the CN3791 solar MPPT charger is
            actively charging. HIGH means no solar charging. Reported to the
            Zigbee coordinator as part of the status payload.

    config WELLD_ADC_OVERSAMPLE_ENABLED
        bool "ADC oversampling (median-of-three)"
        default n
        help
            Take 3 ADS1115 samples per channel and report the median.
            Rejects single-sample noise outliers at the cost of ~4 ms extra
            active time per channel (~12 ms total vs ~4 ms). Enable for
            electrically noisy installations; leave off for maximum battery life.

    config WELLD_TEMP_COMPENSATION_ENABLED
        bool "Temperature compensation for water level"
        default y
        help
            Compensate water-level readings for water density change with
            temperature. Requires CONFIG_WELLD_TEMP_COMPENSATION_PPM_PER_C.
            At 207 ppm/°C the correction is <0.21 % per 10 °C deviation from
            20 °C — small but systematic. Disabled automatically when the
            DS18B20 read fails (guard in main.c: temp > -127.0 °C).

    config WELLD_TEMP_COMPENSATION_PPM_PER_C
        int "Water density coefficient (ppm/°C)"
        default 207
        range 0 500
        depends on WELLD_TEMP_COMPENSATION_ENABLED
        help
            Typical value for fresh water is ~207 ppm/°C. The reported level
            is corrected as: level = raw / (1 + coeff*(temp - 20°C)).

    config WELLD_DS18B20_RESOLUTION_BITS
        int "DS18B20 resolution (bits)"
        default 11
        range 9 12
        help
            Conversion time: 9-bit = 94 ms, 10-bit = 188 ms, 11-bit = 375 ms,
            12-bit = 750 ms. Lower resolution saves active time and battery.
            11-bit gives 0.0625 °C steps — adequate for well water monitoring
            and saves 375 ms per wakeup compared to 12-bit.

endmenu
